myVelibCLUI

Class UserLoop

  • java.lang.Object
    • myVelibCLUI.UserLoop

  • public class UserLoop
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the client application. It handles the CLUI. It contains all the commands and their description, and its main runs an infinite loop.

    The main initialize the CLUI and then allows the user to enter commands.

    The line is then read with the scanner and is split in order to obtain an array of strings.

    The first word is used as the command and the number of elements in the array is counted to obtain the number of parameters.

    If the command is not recognized, it prints an UNRECOGNIZED_COMMAND_MSG. If the command is recognized, the number of parameters is checked.

    If the number of parameters doesn't correspond to the command entered, it prints an INCORRECT_PARAMETERS_NUMBER_MSG.

    If the command and the number of parameters are both good, it calls the right static method from ParsingAndCalling, which will perform the operation and handle the exceptions.

    When it's done, it loops again.

    You can also use commands to read a given txt file or ask to write every outputs to a given txt file

    Also, the loop check at every iteration that the user has not been caught in a deadlock (cannot enter any command and no txt file is read).

    Commands are listed below

    Author:
    Edouard
